quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  35,27,"Seest thou not how that God sendeth down water from the Heaven, and that by it we cause the up-growth of fruits of varied hues, and that on the mountains are tracks of varied hues, white and red, and others are of a raven black"
  35,28,"And of men and reptiles and animals, various likewise are the hues. Such only of his servants as are possessed of knowledge fear God. Lo! God is Mighty, Gracious"
  35,29,"Verily they who recite the Book of God, and observe prayer, and give alms in public and in private from what we have bestowed upon them, may hope for a merchandise that shall not perish"
  35,30,"God will certainly pay them their due wages, and of his bounty increase them: for He is Gracious, Grateful"
  35,31,"And that which we have revealed to thee of the Book is the very Truth, confirmatory of previous Scriptures: for God knoweth and beholdeth his servants"
  35,32,"Moreover, we have made the Book an heritage to those of our servants whom we have chosen. Some of them injure themselves by evil deeds; others keep the midway between good and evil; and others, by the permission of God, outstrip in goodness; this is the great merit"
  35,33,"Into the gardens of Eden shall they enter: with bracelets of gold and pearl shall they be decked therein, and therein shall their raiment be of silk"
  35,34,"And they shall say, \"Praise be to God who hath put away sorrow from us. Verily our Lord is Gracious, Grateful"
  35,35,"Who of His bounty hath placed us in a mansion that shall abide for ever: therein no toil shall reach us, and therein no weariness shall touch us"
  35,36,"But for infidels is the fire of Hell; to die shall never be decreed them, nor shall aught of its torment be made light to them. Thus reward we every infidel"
  35,37,"And therein shall they cry aloud, \"Take us hence, O our Lord! righteousness will we work, and not what we wrought of old.\" - \"Prolonged we not your days that whoever would be warned might be warned therein? And the preacher came to you - Taste it then.\" - There is no protector for the unjust"